
Exactly Where To Change What

Backend code (already done)

OAuth routes are in app.py.

No further code edits needed there.

Backend hosting environment variables (set in your backend host dashboard, not in code)

Go to your backend host env settings (Elastic Beanstalk / Railway / server env panel).

Add/update these keys:

GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET
BACKEND_BASE_URL = https://dxhp0j33db.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/dev (or prod, choose one)
GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI = https://dxhp0j33db.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/dev/auth/google/callback
FRONTEND_SIGNIN_URL = https://your-frontend-domain/signin
FRONTEND_URL = https://your-frontend-domain
Frontend hosting environment variables (set in frontend host dashboard)

Add/update:

REACT_APP_API_URL = same backend base URL
REACT_APP_BASE_API_SERVER = same backend base URL
These are used by frontend code in:

Login.jsx
Signup.jsx
apiRoute.js
Google Cloud Console

Open OAuth Client ID settings.

Set:

Authorized redirect URI = GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI exactly
Authorized JavaScript origin = frontend origin only (example: https://your-frontend-domain)
Important rule

Use one stage only (dev or prod) across all 3 places:

Backend host env
Frontend host env
Google redirect URI
Quick verification after deploy

Open https://dxhp0j33db.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/dev/auth/google/authorize

If it redirects to Google account chooser, config is correct.

